One problem is that following behavior is only applicable in buildkit and not in legacy docker, this needs change in imagebuilder and changing behavior of imagebuilder can disturb legacy docker compat which is not encouraged in past. 

Following patch in imagebuilder fixes the issue but can be merged once there is approval from maintainers ( @nalind WDYT ? ) 

```diff
diff --git a/builder.go b/builder.go
index b01ed0c..76e0df6 100644
--- a/builder.go
+++ b/builder.go
@@ -382,7 +382,10 @@ func (b *Builder) Step() *Step {
        // Include build arguments in the table of variables that we'll use in
        // Resolve(), but override them with values from the actual
        // environment in case there's any conflict.
-       return &Step{Env: mergeEnv(b.Arguments(), mergeEnv(b.Env, b.RunConfig.Env))}
+       // Buildkit-parity: If there are any pre-build ENV and ARG are overlapping give priority to ARG
+       runEnv := mergeEnv(b.Arguments(), b.RunConfig.Env)
+       // Buildkit-parity: Env in builder must take highest priority hence merge again.
+       return &Step{Env: mergeEnv(b.Arguments(), mergeEnv(b.Env, runEnv))}
 }
 ```
